This paper deals with election rules and the aggregation of voter preferences, which falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the use of randomized and deterministic methods for collecting partial preferences, which could be seen as a machine learning (cs.AI) or data science (cs.DS) problem. The theoretical analysis and computer simulations involve algorithms and optimization, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) or social networks (cs.SI).
